 know that you will be late, speak with the raid leader to see if arrangements can be made. If you don't arrive in time, two things can happen.  If the raid leader believes the raid will be successful without your presence, the raid will start and you will miss it.  If the raid leader believes the raid cannot continue without you, you will be penalized on the amount of DKPs you earn from the raid.  The actual amount is dependent upon how long people waited for you to get on.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               Bottom line here is, respect your fellow guild members by thinking ahead and planning ahead.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  One person 15 minutes late in a group of 30 is 7.5 hours of wasted time.  (Note:  The DKP penalty will only be associated with raids that have been planned for ahead of time with a defined start time and meeting location.  Impromptu raids and the like will, of course, not be tied to such a rule.)<br><br>- Act professionally in any situation, whatever it may be.  We will have really good raids and sometimes we will have really bad raids.  This is especially the case when we do new encounters for the first time.  When things get nasty, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               act like an adult.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  We aren't a bunch of bratty children and you are expected to act professionally, even when the crap hits the fan and everyone is pissed off.<br><br>- Raids are not about gaining exp.  You will often lose more exp than you gain.  Groups will be organized to maximize the efficiency of the raiding party and often times there will be only one or two groups that will get any exp.  Please do not complain that your group never gets the kill, but instead focus on helping the raid to be successful.<br><br>- Have any equipment or resist gear that is needed on you at the appointed time. We don't want to hear people asking to borrow gear or have jewelry made for them at the last minute. It's your responsibility to be prepared ahead of time. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               No Gear - No Go!!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>- Everyone is doing his/her job during the event without complaints or whining. If you are a porter you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> port people to the event scene, if you are a buffing class you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> buff people.  If you are a tank and things go badly, you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> die so a cleric can camp. This is your job.<br><br>- No one but the Raid Leader or someone designated by him/her invites other people from outside the guild along. If you have suggestions inform the Raid Leader.<br><br>- Once a raid has started the organizers will make groups and keep you informed on tactics and important orders. We expect everyone to shut up and listen. We realize sometimes people are zoning or miss their group list so these orders will be repeated. At this point please control jokes, horsing around and repeated emotes. This helps not only the organizers but also everyone else who's trying to pay attention. Feel free to relax and mess around before or after a raid but once we're in raid mode please control yourselves.<br><br>- The Raid Leader or the person assigned to make the groups will list the group leader first in a grouping list. Please do not argue with them about whom you're grouped with. We realize some people have slow computers or poor connections and the Raid Leader will try to make sure these people aren't made group leaders. Each group leader is responsible for letting the Raid Leader know the status of their group - when they're all together, mana status, rez status, LD status, lost corpses, etc. - any important information will be relayed to the Raid Leader by each group leader. If the group leader goes LD on a raid the remaining members will regroup ASAP and that new group leader will relay their status to the Raid Leader. This means that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               no other person</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> except the group leaders will be giving information, talking on channel or sending tells to the Raid Leader.<br><br>- Do not question guild leader or raid leader’s decisions during guild events. If you have questions, suggestions, or comments about any decisions, or people, please contact the appropriate person <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>               after</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the guild event.<br><br>- You should attend scheduled guild events if you are online during guild events’ time period. Remember that we are a raiding guild and every member is needed at guild events. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub46.ezboard.com/uslaas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Slaas</A> at: 8/24/01 12:33:53 am<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=7.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showNextMessage?topicID=7.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.sacrosanctguild.com/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.threadControl?topicID=7.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub46.ezboard.com/fdivinity14264frm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=7.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop